text.section:
The regulations may:
apply to any person regulated by the Commissioner under this article or Title 19, Subtitle 7 of the Health - General Article; and
address:
submission of claims or proof of loss;
grace periods for payment of premiums and performance of other duties by insureds;
temporary postponement of cancellations, nonrenewals, premium increases, or policy modifications;
procedures for obtaining nonelective health care services;
time restrictions for filling or refilling prescription drugs;
time frames applicable to an action by the Commissioner under this article; and
any other activity necessary to protect the residents of the State.

section.section:
To activate a regulation adopted under this section, the Commissioner shall issue a bulletin specifying:
that the regulation is activated;
the line or lines of business to which the regulation applies;
the geographic areas to which the regulation applies; and
the period of time for which the regulation applies.
